import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['adjclose'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("What is the trend of the stock prices over time?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['volume'], bins=50)
    plt.xlabel('Volume')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of daily trading volumes?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    plt.bar(data['date'], data['high'], label='High')
    plt.bar(data['date'], data['low'], label='Low')
    
    highest_price = data['high'].max()
    lowest_price = data['low'].min()
    
    plt.axhline(highest_price, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Highest Price: {highest_price:.2f}')
    plt.axhline(lowest_price, color='g', linestyle='--', label=f'Lowest Price: {lowest_price:.2f}')
    
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Price')
    plt.legend()
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title('What is the highest and lowest price of the stock during the given time period?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data['daily_return'] = data['adjclose'].pct_change()
    data['average_daily_return'] = data['daily_return'].mean()
    
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['daily_return'], label='Daily Return')
    plt.axhline(data['average_daily_return'].iloc[0], color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Average Daily Return: {data['average_daily_return'].iloc[0]:.2f}")
    
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Daily Return')
    plt.title('What is the average daily return of the stock?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
